    <link>https://forum.moparisthebest.com/t/redstone-lava-bridge/410169</link>
    <description>Just a quick little something I made. It&#39;s a simple bridge across a pool of lava, powered by redstone and sticky pistons.

Unpowered:
[IMG]http://i1115.photobucket.com/albums/k557/Lord_Zymus/2011-08-14_155305.png[/img]

Circuit:
[IMG]http://i1115.photobucket.com/albums/k557/Lord_Zymus/2011-08-14_155940.png[/img]

Powered:
[IMG]http://i1115.photobucket.com/albums/k557/Lord_Zymus/2011-08-14_160003.png[/img]

Cross-section while powered:
[IMG]http://i1115.photobucket.com/albums/k557/Lord_Zymus/2011-08-14_160039.png[/img]

You&#39;ll notice that every 4th block is just one column of cobblestone. I designed it this way because it simplified the repeater process (otherwise the number of repeaters you would increase by 4 for each section))

I used 2 blocks of lava on each side of each step.

If you need any more explanation, I would be happy to provide.</description>
    
